  "poem": {
    "content": "The baby sleeps, a coral dream,\nSafe within a cubic room,\nWhere moonbeams drip like honey slow,\nAnd shadows decorate the gloom.\n\nTo either swing, or gently hold,\nA nuclear heart beats soft and low,\nWe aim to achieve a calmer state,\nBefore the darker seeds will grow.\n\nThey say to decide, to make a choice,\nTo bring some order to the tide,\nBut calm is lost, a fleeting grace,\nWhen fear threatens from inside.\n\nLet not the harshness of the world\nInflict such pain, so deep and wide.\nInstead, let kindness gently flow,\nAnd push the heavy fears aside.\n\nThe coral fades, the dream takes hold,\nA future shaped, a story told.",
